Sentencas: In this study, we investigate the effects of adding titanium dioxide (TiO2) and samarium doped cerium oxide (SDC) on the properties of yttrium-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte.
Titulo: Effects of TiO2 and SDC addition on the properties of YSZ electrolyte

Sentencas: The microstructure, mechanical, and electrochemical properties of the electrolyte are investigated.
Titulo: Effects of TiO2 and SDC addition on the properties of YSZ electrolyte

Sentencas: The performance in CO2 electrolysis is measured by supplying carbon dioxide to Ni-YSZ electrode and nitrogen to LSM electrode.
Titulo: Effects of TiO2 and SDC addition on the properties of YSZ electrolyte

Sentencas: Results show that TiO2 and SDC addition can reduce the sintering temperature and increase grain size.
Titulo: Effects of TiO2 and SDC addition on the properties of YSZ electrolyte

Sentencas: The ionic conductivity is 0.123 S cm(-1) at 1000 degrees C.
Titulo: Effects of TiO2 and SDC addition on the properties of YSZ electrolyte

Sentencas: In addition, the thermal expansion coefficient at 1000 degrees C is 8.25 x 10(-6)K(-1).
Titulo: Effects of TiO2 and SDC addition on the properties of YSZ electrolyte

Sentencas: The current density of the cell is 439 mA cm(-2) at 1.3 V and 1000 degrees C in solid oxide electrolysis cell.
